{
  "doc_id": "44225",
  "text": "A number of studies were performed in various VANET environments to estimate the channel by performing measurements and fitting the measured data using well-known models (e.g., log-distance path loss [CITATION_1] ). For example, Paschalidis et al. in [CITATION_2] performed measurements in different environments (urban, suburban, rural, highway) and fitted the measurements data to the log-distance path loss model. The path loss exponent (PLE) varied considerably (between 1.83 and 3.59) for different locations and LOS conditions. The large range of PLE values goes to show that a single PLE value can not capture the characteristics of a channel, even for a single location/environment. Therefore, different link types (LOS, NLOSv, NLOSb) need to be distinguished and modeled separately.",
